## Backend Structure (Python FastAPI)

### Project Layout
```
api/
├── main.py                 # FastAPI app entry point
├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies
├── seed_data.py           # Database seeding script
└── app/
    ├── core/
    │   ├── config.py      # Application settings
    │   ├── database.py    # SQLAlchemy setup
    │   └── security.py    # JWT & password hashing
    ├── models/
    │   └── __init__.py    # SQLAlchemy models
    ├── schemas.py         # Pydantic schemas
    └── api/
        └── v1/            # API endpoints
            ├── __init__.py
            ├── auth.py
            ├── calculators.py
            ├── calculation_results.py
            ├── profiles.py
            └── health.py
```

### Key Files

**api/main.py** - FastAPI application with CORS and lifespan management
**api/app/core/config.py** - Settings (DATABASE_URL, SECRET_KEY, etc.)
**api/app/core/database.py** - Async SQLAlchemy engine and session
**api/app/core/security.py** - JWT token creation and password hashing
**api/app/models/__init__.py** - Database models (User, Calculator, CalculationResult, etc.)
**api/app/schemas.py** - Pydantic request/response models
**api/seed_data.py** - Seeds database with initial calculator data

### Running Backend

```bash
# Install dependencies
cd api && python3 -m pip install -r requirements.txt

# Seed database
python3 seed_data.py

# Start server
npm run start-backend
# or directly:
cd api && python3 -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 3001 --reload
```

## Important Notes

### Demo File Management
- `components/Demo.tsx` is ONLY for early development preview with fake data - NEVER copy its content to real screens
- Once ANY real screen exists, you MUST delete Demo.tsx immediately
- NEVER reference or link to Demo.tsx in production features - create real screens with real data instead
- Demo serves as temporary placeholder until real screens are developed
- `app/_layout.tsx` automatically detects and renders Demo.tsx if it exists

### Code Quality Standards
- Keep dependencies minimal and well-documented
- Use TypeScript strictly - avoid `any` type when possible
- Follow semantic naming conventions

### DO NOT
- Use fake data that should come from API/database
- Create business logic in demo screens
- Use direct color values (white, black, etc.) - use semantic tokens only
- Skip testing before delivery
- Commit code with lint errors or failing tests
